dct_title_s: Illinois-Indiana-Kentucky, New Haven quadrangle [1939 reprint without vegetation]
dct_description_sm: United States, Department of the Interior, Geological Survey , State of Illinois, Department of Registration and Education, Geological Survey Division , State of Kentucky , H.M. Wilson, geographer , Chas. E. Cooke, in charge of section , topography by W.J. Lloyd and L. Scott Smith. Filing title: New Haven, Ill.-Ind.-Ky. Edition of 1906, reprinted 1939. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Contour interval 20 feet. Shows portions of Gallatin and White counties, Illinois, Posey County, Indiana, and Union County, Kentucky. Surveyed in 1905. Culture revised in part, 1938. Road data 1939.
Dimensions: 45 x 42 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:62,500
